const description = "KitchenAid refrigerator repair across LA, OC, Ventura. KRFC400, KRFC300, KBSD608, KBFN506, KRMF706. Whirlpool family. $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is KitchenAid the same company as Whirlpool?",
    a: "Whirlpool Corporation has owned KitchenAid since 1986. KitchenAid maintains its premium-positioned identity within the Whirlpool family alongside Whirlpool (mid-tier), Maytag (mid-tier value), and JennAir (premium-positioned). Same parent corporation, different price tiers and aesthetic positioning. KitchenAid shares many components with sister brands, which is good news for parts availability."
  },
  {
    q: "My KitchenAid ice maker isn't working. What's wrong?",
    a: "Most common cause: ice maker module failure (Whirlpool family ice maker, common 4 to 7 year service item). Less common: water inlet valve failed, water filter clogged, or freezer compartment too warm. We diagnose all of these in a single visit and stock the Whirlpool family ice maker module on the van."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service KRFC400ESS, KRFC300ESS, KBSD608ESS, KBFN506ESS?",
    a: "Yes. These are our most common KitchenAid service calls. Common parts (ice maker modules, water inlet valves, damper actuators, door gaskets) on the van. KRFC400ESS specifically is the most popular KitchenAid mid-premium model in LA mid-tier renovations."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do KitchenAid refrigerators last?",
    a: "10 to 14 years typical with proper maintenance. Compressor is usually the limiting factor. Coastal installs (Manhattan Beach, Marina del Rey, Newport Beach, Pacific Palisades) shorter due to salt-air condenser load (8 to 12 years). Premium repair through year 12 makes sense; replacement equivalent runs $4,000 to $7,000+, so major repairs through year 12 typically pencil out."
  },
  {
    q: "My KitchenAid freezer is fine but the fridge is warm. What's wrong?",
    a: "Classic damper actuator failure. KitchenAid uses single-evaporator architecture with damper transfer (most modern fridges except Sub-Zero). Damper actuator fails, cold air doesn't transfer to the fridge compartment, and you get fridge warm with freezer cold. Year 7 to 10 typical failure. Replacement runs $260 to $420."
  },
  {
    q: "My KitchenAid uses R-600a refrigerant. What's that?",
    a: "R-600a (isobutane) is hydrocarbon refrigerant in newer KitchenAid models (post-2018 transition). Different service procedures than R-134a. Requires R-600a awareness and proper handling procedures (R-600a is a flammable hydrocarbon). Most appliance shops don't have R-600a training. We do."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty. KitchenAid component warranties (where applicable through Whirlpool family service network) processed separately. CSLB #1138898 and BBB A+. EPA 608 Universal certified for sealed-system refrigerant work."
  }
];

