<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">KitchenAid service</p>
    <h2>Why KitchenAid is the most popular mid-premium refrigerator brand in LA.</h2>

    <p>KitchenAid is the most popular mid-premium refrigerator brand in LA. Whirlpool Corporation has owned KitchenAid since 1986, but the brand maintains its premium-positioned identity within the Whirlpool family alongside Whirlpool (mid-tier), Maytag (mid-tier value), and JennAir (premium-positioned). Most LA-area mid-premium kitchen remodels (Pasadena, Studio City, Sherman Oaks, Encino, Long Beach, Beverly Hills mid-tier homes) feature KitchenAid refrigerators because the price-to-quality balance is right: $3,000 to $7,000 typical pricing, stainless steel finishes, reliable Whirlpool engineering, excellent parts availability through Whirlpool's largest-in-industry US distribution network.</p>

    <p>We service the entire KitchenAid refrigerator lineup across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>KRFC Series</strong> counter-depth French door (KRFC400ESS, the most popular KitchenAid model: 36" French door 19.5 cu ft with stainless steel; KRFC300ESS, KRFC604FSS multi-door variant). <strong>KRFF Series</strong> full-depth French door (KRFF305ESS 25 cu ft, KRFF577KPS). <strong>KBSD Series</strong> built-in side-by-side (KBSD606ESS 30", KBSD608ESS 36", KBSD618ESS 42"). <strong>KRSC Series</strong> counter-depth side-by-side (KRSC503ESS). <strong>KBFN Series</strong> built-in bottom-freezer (KBFN506ESS 30", KBFN508ESS 36"). <strong>KRMF Series</strong> 5-door multi-door (KRMF706ESS).</p>

    <p>$89 residential diagnostic, waived with repair. CSLB #1138898. <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608 Universal certified</a> for R-134a and R-600a sealed-system work. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Series-aware diagnosis</p>
    <h2>The KitchenAid lineup, and what fails by series.</h2>

    <p class="lead">KitchenAid uses a clear product hierarchy across French door (KRFC counter-depth, KRFF full-depth), built-in side-by-side (KBSD), counter-depth side-by-side (KRSC), built-in bottom-freezer (KBFN), and multi-door (KRMF) formats. Diagnostics share Whirlpool family architecture across all series.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">KRFC Series Counter-Depth French Door (Most Popular)</h3>
    <p>KRFC400ESS is the dominant KitchenAid mid-premium model in LA. 36" French door with stainless steel, 19.5 cu ft counter-depth design, includes ice maker and water dispenser. KRFC300ESS adds a full lower freezer drawer. KRFC604FSS adds a 4th door (additional snack/produce zone).</p>
    <p>Common failures in chronological order:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 4 to 7:</strong> Ice maker module issues (Whirlpool family ice maker, common across Whirlpool/Maytag/KitchenAid). Replacement $290 to $540.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5 to 8:</strong> Water inlet valve diaphragm degraded.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6 to 9:</strong> Door gasket compression (lower than Sub-Zero gasket life but reasonable for the tier).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 7 to 10:</strong> Damper actuator failure (classic single-evap fridge pattern: fridge warm, freezer cold).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8 to 12:</strong> Defrost system failure (timer, heater, or board; modern KitchenAid has integrated defrost board).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10 to 14:</strong> Compressor mechanical wear, replace-vs-repair decision based on remaining cabinet condition.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">KRFF Series Full-Depth French Door</h3>
    <p>KRFF305ESS, KRFF577KPS. Same architecture as KRFC but full-depth for more interior space. Common in kitchens where counter-depth aesthetic is less critical. Same failure patterns as KRFC.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">KBSD Series Built-In Side-by-Side</h3>
    <p>KBSD606ESS (30"), KBSD608ESS (36"), KBSD618ESS (42"). Built-in installations with premium aesthetic, panel-ready or stainless steel finishes. Same internal architecture but built-in installation adds installation-related issues (door gap drift, hinge alignment with cabinet). Side-by-side configuration means fridge and freezer have independent doors with separate gaskets.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">KBFN Series Built-In Bottom-Freezer</h3>
    <p>KBFN506ESS (30"), KBFN508ESS (36"). Built-in with lower freezer drawer. Premium aesthetic. Same failure profile with additional freezer drawer slide service items at year 6 to 10.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">KRMF Series 5-Door Multi-Door and KRSC Counter-Depth Side-by-Side</h3>
    <p>KRMF706ESS: 5-door multi-door (French door + lower freezer drawer + snack drawer). Multiple temperature zones add complexity to thermostat and damper architecture: more potential service items, but also more flexibility. KRSC503ESS: 25 cu ft counter-depth side-by-side, same failure profile as KBSD without the built-in installation work.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TYPICAL REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top KitchenAid repairs we see in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on KitchenAid service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Ice maker module replacement.</strong> Whirlpool family ice maker. Year 4 to 7 typical. Common van-stocked part.</li>
      <li><strong>Water inlet valve replacement.</strong> Water dispenser issues or ice maker water issues. Year 5 to 8 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket replacement.</strong> Whirlpool family gaskets. Year 6 to 9 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Damper actuator.</strong> Fridge warm, freezer cold pattern. Common year 7 to 10 service. Practitioner-level pattern recognition matters here.</li>
      <li><strong>Water filter replacement.</strong> EveryDrop filter system (Whirlpool family standard). Every 6 months. Hard water areas more often.</li>
      <li><strong>Condenser fan motor.</strong> Year 6 to 10 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Evaporator fan motor.</strong> Year 7 to 10 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Defrost system service.</strong> Defrost timer, heater, or board. Year 8 to 12 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Compressor replacement.</strong> Year 10 to 14 cost-vs-replace decision.</li>
      <li><strong>Whirlpool family parts compatibility leverage.</strong> KitchenAid shares many components with Whirlpool, Maytag, JennAir. Excellent parts availability and pricing.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five KitchenAid jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pasadena · KitchenAid KRFC400ESS 36" French door (7 years, R-134a)</h3>
        <p>Fridge warm, freezer cold. Diagnostic confirmed: damper actuator failed plus evaporator fan motor showing wear (cascading failure typical at the 7-year mark). Replaced both in single visit. Total: $89 plus $345 parts plus $290 labor = $724.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Studio City · KitchenAid KBSD608ESS 36" built-in side-by-side (9 years, R-134a)</h3>
        <p>Ice maker not making ice. Diagnostic: ice maker module degraded (Whirlpool family ice maker, common 4 to 7 year service). Replaced module. Tested ice maker through 4 ice cycles. Total: $89 plus $390 module plus 1 hour labor = $479.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills · KitchenAid KBFN508ESS 36" built-in bottom-freezer (6 years, R-134a)</h3>
        <p>Freezer drawer not closing fully and freezer warming. Diagnostic: drawer gasket compressed at hinge side plus drawer slide friction high (drawer not seating fully against gasket). Replaced freezer drawer gasket plus lubricated drawer slides. Total: $89 plus $260 gasket plus $290 labor = $639.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Encino · KitchenAid KRMF706ESS 5-door multi-door (5 years, R-134a)</h3>
        <p>Middle "produce" zone running too cold. Diagnostic: zone-specific damper drift (multi-door multi-zone designs have separate zone dampers). Recalibrated produce zone damper (no parts replacement needed, calibration adjustment). Total: $89 plus 1.5 hours labor = $269. Quick fix without parts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Long Beach · KitchenAid KRFC300ESS 36" French door with lower freezer drawer (8 years, R-134a)</h3>
        <p>Water on floor in front of fridge. Diagnostic: defrost drain blocked (most common cause of "water on floor": defrost water from freezer evaporator can't drain and overflows). Cleared defrost drain. No parts needed. Total: $89 plus 30 min labor = $209.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

